accessibility.text: Lambda works best when loads are short and bursty.  If the server is continually getting called, then it’s worth considering a full time VM or even hosting your own.
Can’t hold persistent storage.  A lot of chattiness between the database and the different Lambda nodes.
Responses can only be so large.  By default, AWS only allows HTTP responses to be 6MB in size and Lambda functions to run for a max of 10 seconds per request (can increase with some modification).
Be careful of infinite loops and forking!
